(2, 1, 'Allow vehicles on the widest bridge in Vietnam', '<span class="noidungtomtat"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: #CCFFFF; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">According to the\r\n plan of Hanoi Peopleâ€™s Committee, on the nex Sep,26<sup>th </sup>, Vinh\r\n Tuy bridge - the widest bridge inVietnam will officially allow \r\nvehicles. Vinh Tuy bridge crosses over the Red River with 5.8 km length \r\nincluding the length crossing river of 3.7 km, bridge surface with<span>&nbsp;\r\n </span>19m width (phase 1).</font></span></span>', 'hjtyvinht.png', '<span class="noidungtomtat"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: #CCFFFF; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">Total investment\r\n capital of the project is 3598 billion dong, of which, the building \r\npart is 1830 billion dong, the rest is the cost of clearance and \r\nprovision ... The project has moved 1568 households and 13 agencies in \r\nthe area of<span>&nbsp; </span>2 districts Long Bien and Hai Ba Trung in past\r\n four years. The project will complete in June 2010. <br>\r\n<br>Phase 1, to save costs, \r\n<st1:city w:st="on">\r\n<st1:place w:st="on">Hanoi</st1:place></st1:city> city carried out to \r\nbuild bridge surface with 19m width, but the roads linking the bridge \r\nwith 38m width. Phase 2 in the future will continue to expand bridge \r\nsurface as planned. <br>\r\n<br>According to experts on traffic, Vinh Tuy bridge is<span>&nbsp; </span>efficient\r\n support for the Chuong Duong bridge. This is the inner city bridge, \r\nlinking the Vinh Tuy ward (Hai Ba Trung) to Phuc Dong ward (Long Bien \r\ndistrict). <br>\r\n<br>As planned, the vehicle traffic on the area of<span>&nbsp; </span>Long \r\nBien district and the north of Vinh Tuy bridge will be made as follows: <br>\r\n<br>For vehicles with loading capacity under 10 tons, motorcycles, \r\nmotorbikes can follow the right of Red dyke and Thach Ban route, head \r\nroute in the industry Hanel industrial zone is connected to the routes \r\nof the Vinh Tuy bridge project to go over the bridge to Minh Khai. The \r\nvehicles when going on the<span>&nbsp; </span>right head of Red dyke, Thach \r\nBan road into the project of Vinh Tuy bridge will not turn on traffic \r\nhead in an Hanel industrial zone and vice versa. <br>\r\n<br>Means with loading capacity<span>&nbsp; </span>over 10 tons must go to \r\nNguyen Van Linh street, then go to the main axis in the Hanel industrial\r\n zone<span>&nbsp; </span>connecting to the project to go through the Minh \r\nKhai and they will not be allowed to return to the Thach Ban route. <br>\r\n<br>The transportation from the Long Bien crossing over bridge, entering\r\n the inner city can turn down Nguyen Khoai dyke or go straight to\r\n<st1:street w:st="on">\r\n<st1:address w:st="on">Nguyen Minh Khai street</st1:address></st1:street>\r\n to go into the inner city. The means to go down the south have to go \r\nstraight to\r\n<st1:street w:st="on">\r\n<st1:address w:st="on">Minh Khai street</st1:address></st1:street> to \r\nturn down\r\n<st1:street w:st="on">\r\n<st1:address w:st="on">Tam Chinh street</st1:address></st1:street>. \r\nParticularly, for the vehicles turn on the\r\n<st1:place w:st="on">\r\n<st1:placename w:st="on">Chuong</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placename w:st="on">Duong</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placetype w:st="on">Bridge</st1:placetype></st1:place> will turn \r\ndown\r\n<st1:street w:st="on">\r\n<st1:address w:st="on">CV1C street</st1:address></st1:street>. <br>\r\n<br>The vehicles on streets of Hai Ba Trung district and the south of \r\nVinh Tuy bridge to go to area of Long Bien district and the north, \r\nspecifically as follows: The inner city transportation or from the south\r\n can go on Minh Khai routes to pass through Long Bien. For the vehicles \r\nfrom the Thanh Tri<span>&nbsp; </span>can go up bridge by going on the Nguyen\r\n Khoai dyke and turn on CV1B branch<span>&nbsp; </span>to go up the bridge. <br>\r\n<br>The vehicles from Chuong Duong bridge towards Vinh Tuy bridge will \r\ngo pass space under the bridge to turn to the CV1A branch to go up the \r\nbridge. After the vehicles were on the bridge, theywill need to go as \r\nthe folowing directions: The truck under 10 tons and primitivety, can \r\nturn on roads in Hanel industrial zone;\r\n<st1:street w:st="on">\r\n<st1:address w:st="on">Thanh Ban street</st1:address></st1:street> amd \r\nRed right dyke to go to many directions . Particularly,the vehicles over\r\n 10 tons are required to go to Hanel routes to turn to Nguyen Van Linh \r\nfor places.\r\n</font></span></span>', 'CTN Viet Nam', '16/06/2010', 1, 1, 0),
(3, 2, ' Lai Chau hydropower: Have to be controlled independently ', '<span class="noidungtomtat"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: #CCFFFF; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">At the \r\nconference<span>&nbsp; </span>of reporting monitoring Lai Chau hydropower \r\nproject today (21 / 9), Committee for Science, Technology and \r\nEnvironment of the National Assembly proposed to use independent \r\nconsultants to monitor the design process as well as execute this major \r\nwork.</font></span></span>', 'fewrtevinh.png', '<span class="noidungtomtat"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: #CCFFFF; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">Lai Chau \r\nhydropower project in the list of projects of<span>&nbsp; </span>national \r\nelectricity development Planning<span>&nbsp; </span>in the period of 2006 - \r\n2015, which considered to 2025, the Prime Minister<span>&nbsp; </span>approved\r\n in 2007. <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<st1:country-region w:st="on">\r\n<st1:place w:st="on">Vietnam</st1:place></st1:country-region>''s \r\nelectricity demand increased rapidly the past years, every 1% of GDP, \r\nthe electricity demand increased by 2%. Expected that\r\n<st1:country-region w:st="on">\r\n<st1:place w:st="on">Vietnam</st1:place></st1:country-region> lacks \r\nabout 23.8 billion kwh in 2015, about 104.1 billion Kwh in 2020. <br>\r\n<br>Over 32 trillion dong<br>\r\n<br>Lai Chau hydropower is the top echelon of Da River mainstream, on \r\nthe upper echelon of the Son La hydropower under construction. The work \r\nis expected to be built at Nam Hang commune, Muong Te district, Lai Chau\r\n province. With total preliminary investment estimated at more than 32 \r\ntrillion dong, the design of electricity in the average level reached \r\n4704 million kwh, the progress made in 9 years. <br>\r\n<br>According to Deputy Minister of Industry and Trade Do Huu Hao, this \r\nis a hydropower work that not only plays an important role in the \r\ndevelopment of electricity and water supply for the Red River Delta in \r\nthe dry season, but also creates opportunities for socio- economic \r\ndevelopment for the two provinces of Lai Chau and Dien Bien for \r\nguaranteeing security and defence for the northwest area.<br>\r\nAfter investigating the project preliminarily, Deputy Chairman of the \r\nCommittee for Science, Technology and Environment of the National \r\nAssembly, Nghiem Vu Khai noted: "It is necessary to use independent \r\nconsultant to monitor in the process of design and construction to avoid\r\n cracking the RCC dam<span>&nbsp; </span>in the collap event<span>&nbsp; </span>in\r\n Can Tho Bridgeâ€. <br>\r\nMr. Khai also raise the problem of guaranteeing national defence \r\nsecurity - security in the process of implementing this project. Lai \r\nChau hydropower belongs to the the most upper level of the Da river, \r\nbordering the Chinese border. Designed by selecting the 295 meter height\r\n ,that will ensure water level from the border around 15-20 km, but when\r\n overflowing water or flood, the dam is away to the border about 2 km. \r\nMr Khai proposed the agency to have the specific plan for ensuring \r\nsecurity and safety when the flood occurs. <br>\r\nSettlement relocation <br>\r\nBeing the major work, but Lai Chau hydropower has the mass of<span>&nbsp; </span>migration\r\n and resettlement which is not large. Expected that about \r\n1331households/5.867 inhabitans belongs to Muong Te district, Lai Chau \r\nprovince being within the scope of the lake and the workâ€™s space. <br>\r\nThe project investor- the Electricity Group of\r\n<st1:country-region w:st="on">\r\n<st1:place w:st="on">Vietnam</st1:place></st1:country-region> - has set \r\nup compensation costs, migration and resettlement of this work in \r\naccordance with the mechanism of Son La hydropower . Although the Deputy\r\n Minister Do Huu Hao said "Compensation cost will be higher, but the \r\ncost of migration and resettlement of this work is estimated less than \r\n10% of the cost of migration and resettlement of Son La hydroelectric \r\nproject. <br>\r\nEven so, the units involved project assessment note to evaluate and \r\nanalyze existing and disadvantages in the process of implementing two \r\nprojects in Hoa Binh and Son La<span>&nbsp; </span>in order that immigrant \r\nresettlement satisfied. <br>\r\nBefore officially starting construction in the end of 2010, the project \r\nwill be launched at the National Assembly session to get opinions this \r\nlater year. Estimated that Lai Chau hydropower will generate power<span>&nbsp;\r\n </span>the end machine unit in 2010 and complete the work in 2017.\r\n</font></span></span>', 'CTN Viet Nam', '16/06/2010', 1, 1, 0),
(4, 1, '2014: Operating the largest hydroelectricity in Kon Tum', '<span class="noidungtomtat"><p align="justify"><font color="#666666"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;">Upper Kontum</span><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;"> upper Hydropower was \r\nfitted two machine units with total capacity of 220 MW, 90.8 MW \r\nguarantee capacity, electronic average volume reached 1.1 billion KWh \r\nper year with the total of<span>&nbsp; </span>5744 billion investment \r\ncapital. <span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">Morning 27/9, in Kon Plong district (Kon Tum)</font></span></span></font></p></span>', 'gdfgrnh1.png', '<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tbody><tr><tr><td valign="top"><div align="left"><span class="noidungtomtat"><p align="justify"><font color="#666666"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;">Upper Kontum</span><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;"> upper Hydropower was \r\nfitted two machine units with total capacity of 220 MW, 90.8 MW \r\nguarantee capacity, electronic average volume reached 1.1 billion KWh \r\nper year with the total of<span>&nbsp; </span>5744 billion investment \r\ncapital. <span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">Morning 27/9, in Kon Plong district (Kon Tum)</font></span></span></font></p></span>\r\n                                  <span class="noidungtomtat"><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;" align="justify"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">Vinh Son - Song Hinh Hydropower joint-stock Company&nbsp; \r\nHas started construction of Upper Kon Tum. This is the largest \r\nhydroelectric<span>&nbsp; </span>in Kon Tum ever, is the hydroelectric work \r\nof grade II - projects in Group A. \r\n<o:p></o:p></font></span>\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;" align="justify"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;"><font color="#666666">Upper Kontum Hydropower <span style="color: black;">hydroelectric on DakSnghe river â€“ a branch of \r\nDacBla river (branch level 1 of Se San river). The<span>&nbsp; </span>clue \r\nwork group and<span>&nbsp; </span>water reservoir </span>of 2 communes \r\nincluding Dak Koi (Kon Ray district) and Dak Tang (district Kon Plong)<span>&nbsp;\r\n </span>of Kon Tum province. <br>\r\nUpper Kontum Hydropower with the main task is to exploit hydropower of \r\n<st1:place w:st="on">\r\n<st1:placename w:st="on">Snghe</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placename w:st="on">Dak</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placetype w:st="on">River</st1:placetype></st1:place> to provide \r\nelectricity to 220 KV grid of the national electricity system. In \r\naddition, the work also adds stable water resource to the\r\n<st1:place w:st="on">\r\n<st1:placename w:st="on">Tra</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placename w:st="on">Khuc</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placetype w:st="on">River</st1:placetype></st1:place> (Quang Ngai) \r\nto meet residentsâ€™needs, agriculture and industry in the lower area. <br>\r\nUpper Kontum Hydropower will be completed and put the two mechano units \r\ninto operation in 2014 .\r\n<o:p></o:p></font></span></p></span>		  \r\n                       	</div></td></tr></tr></tbody></table>', 'CTN Viet Nam', '16/06/2010', 1, 1, 0),
